{"name": "mltipy", "metadata": {"name": "mltipy", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["realtime", "websockets"], "summary": "Multiplayer w/ Supabase Realtime Python", "upload_time": 1733827651}, "documentation": ["# Multipy\n\nMake multiplayer in Python simple!\n\n## Quick Intro\n\n### Install it\n\n```shell\npip install realtime mltipy\n```\n\n### And use it\n\n```py\n\nimport multipy\n\n# Create a new client\n# Initialize by passing the Project ID and key...\nclient = multipy.Client((\"<PROJECT ID>\", \"<API KEY>\"))\n\n# ...Or use a `.env`\n### .env ###\n# PROJECT_ID=<PROJECT_ID>\n# API_KEY=<API KEY>\nclient = multipy.Client(open(\"./.env\"))\n\nasync def main():\n    client.set_username('client1')\n    await client.activate()\n\n    await client.join_room('<ROOM NAME>')\n    await client.listen()\n\n    # Recieve some stuff..\n    @client.on_event(\"msg\")\n    def on_msg(payload):\n        print(payload)\n    \n    # Or send some!\n    await client.send_event\n\n    # Do Stuff...\n    await client.terminate()\n    # or use this\n    -client\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "multipy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "multipy.Client", "xref": {"fqname": "multipy.multipy.Client", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "multipy.multipy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "multipy.multipy.LETTERS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "multipy.multipy.PLAYER_LIMIT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "multipy.multipy.Client", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "multipy.multipy.Client.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "auth", "type": {"name": "tuple[str, str] | TextIO", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "multipy.multipy.Client.__neg__", "asynchronous":